1 3. "Minor" means an unmarried person under eighteen (18) years
2 of age; and
3 4. "Public place" means any area or space that the general
4 public may freely access without payment for admission; provided,
5 however, any place that limits access pursuant to an admissions
6 process or that restricts minors from entering the area or space to
7 participate or take part in any event shall be exempt from the
8 provisions of this section.
9 B. 1. It shall be unlawful for a person to engage in an adult
10 performance which contains obscene material, or for any political
11 subdivision of this state to allow, permit, organize, or authorize
12 the viewing of an adult performance which contains obscene material,
13 on public property or in a public place where a minor, as part of
14 the general public, will be exposed to view such adult performance.
15 2. A political subdivision acting in good faith in accordance
16 with the requirements of this subsection shall not be liable for the
17 acts of an individual or group in violation of this subsection.
18 C. Any person who violates the provisions of subsection B of
19 this section shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
20 punishable by imprisonment in a county jail for a term not exceeding
21 one (1) year, or by a fine of not less than Five Hundred Dollars
22 ($500.00) and not exceeding One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by
23 both such fine and imprisonment.
